<FIRST>r i PM-SoloVoyage     05-03 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Solo Voyage,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sailer Claims Record For Fastest Round-The-World Solo Sail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BREST, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   French yachtsman Olivier de Kersauzon
sailed into this Atlantic port this morning 125 days and 19 hours
after his departure, claiming a record for the fastest solo sailing
voyage around the world.
   Kersauzon left Brest Dec. 28 in his pink-colored trimaran named
Another Look. He made two stops along the way for repairs, first in
South Africa and then in Argentina.
   On his triumphant return at 8:25 a.m. today, Kersauzon was
escorted by several French naval vessels. Fireboats sounded their
sirens and sprayed jets of water in the air in salute.
   The previous record of 129 days, 19 hours was set in 1987 by
Philippe Monnet, also of France.
