<FIRST>r i PM-Gypsies     05-03 0188</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Gypsies,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gypsy Leader Says Romanian Guards Allegedly Killed Gypsies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The World Gypsy Congress said today
it had unconfirmed reports that about 50 Romanian Gypsies were
killed by Romanian border guards after they tried to escape to
Hungary.
   The incident purportedly took place a month ago. The secretary
of the Gypsy Congress, Rajko Djuric, said the claims prompted Gypsy
leaders to launch an international campaign to investigate the
report.
   ``We do not know exactly the date or the place, but several
different sources provided enough details for us to conclude that
the report about this massacre is true,'' Djuric told The
Associated Press.
   ``They came to the Hungarian border at night and crossed it
illegally. But, since they were anthropologically easily
recognizable _ for their darker complexion _ the Hungarians turned
them back,'' Djuric alleged.
   ``Once back on the Romanian side of the border they were mowed
down by Romanian armed border guards,'' he said.
   Djuric called for a commission of European parliaments to help
investigate the allegations and said he was alerting the United
Nations and the Helsinki Federation for Human Rights.
</TEXT>
