<FIRST>r i AM-China-Earthquake     05-03 0201</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-China-Earthquake,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Strong Quake Shakes Southwest China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The third strong earthquake in less than a month
shook southwest China's Sichuan province on Wednesday, injuring two
road workers, the official Xinhua News Agency said.
   It said the workemen were digging a ditch when they were hit by
a rockslide, but did not say how seriously they were hurt.
   The quake was centered near Batang County, which was the
epicenter of strong earthquakes on April 16 and April 25 that
killed 11 people.
   The latest earthquake measured 6.4 on the Richter scale,
signifying a quake capable of causing severe damage in a populated
area. The scale is a gauge of the energy released by an earthquake
as measured by the ground motion recorded on a seismograph. The two
earlier quakes each measured 6.7 on the scale.
   The highway linking Sichuan's capital of Chengdu to Batang was
blocked by a rockslide and two trucks carrying relief materials
were hit by rocks, Xinhua said.
   It said no one was killed in the quake because residents had
been warned to expect further temblors.
   China's worst earthquake in 12 years struck Yunnan province
south of Sichuan on Nov. 6 and killed 730 people.
</TEXT>
