<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--DirectoryRecall     05-03 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Directory Recall,0171</SECOND>
<HEAD>30,000 Phone Books Recalled For Listing Shelter Address</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GTE Florida Inc. is sending workers
door-to-door in portions of two counties this week to collect
telephone books that mistakenly included the address of a spouse
abuse shelter.
   The company said about 30,000 books were recalled in Pasco and
Pinellas counties. Another 60,000 directories were printed with the
error but never distributed, said GTE public affairs manager Bruce
Kotchey.
   Distribution began last Thursday. GTE ordered the recall Friday
after learning the address, which the shelter requested not be
listed, was included.
   GTE feared angry husbands would be able to find the center and
attack women who went there for help, Kotchey said. The spokesman
blamed the mistake on ``human error somewhere along the line.''
   The phone company hopes to begin distribution in two weeks of
corrected directories.
   GTE representatives and directors of the shelter are discussing
ways, including additional shelter security, to blunt the effects
of the listing, Kotchey said.
</TEXT>
