<HEAD>Pepper Changes Hospitals for Care</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Claude Pepper, the eldest member of
Congress, has entered Johns Hopkins Hospital in Baltimore where he
can be under the care of a prominent specialist in gastrointestinal
problems, his office said Wednesday.
   The 88-year-old Pepper, D-Fla., had been under treatment for a
``digestive disturbance'' at Walter Reed Medical Center since April
6 before checking into Johns Hopkins on Tuesday, his office said.
   The announcement said Pepper consulted Dr. John H. Hendrix on
April 25 at the physician's office at Johns Hopkins and
subsequently decided to place himself under Hendrix' care.
   President Bush visited with Pepper for about 20 minutes last
Sunday.
   The announcement from Pepper's office said, ``While Pepper
appreciates the many inquiries and good wishes he has received, he
has decided to release no further information about his health at
this time.''
